Summary:
Hello everyone! I'm a maple syrup wolf. Didn't do anything the first two nights. 

N3, I regretfully munched on Santa to avoid starvation. My clock is reset, and I shouldn't need to kill until N6 I believe. 

~~~~~~

No matter how hard you try, sometimes it just doesn't work out. And you know what? That's fine! Because I know that everyone else is trying just as hard as me. It doesn't matter what role, team, or even game it is. If we all try our best, that's when the true spirit of werewolf really comes out. If you could try hard and win every single game, I doubt anyone would play. Because at the end of the day, it's not about winning and losing. It's about playing with the best of em. Making mistakes, killing intel roles as a maple wolf, and just totally messing up is fine. Ya know what, it's better than fine! It's perfect. Every mistake is a learning experience, and let's just say I'm a quick learner. I think we all are to some extent. We all mess up, we all make mistakes, bad reads, bad plays etc. But that's okay! We are all learning together and growing as a community. With every mistake we grow stronger. Next game, I will do better. And I know you will too! 

Signed
-Kirsch
